Football Events

1/2/2018

  • In order to perform analysis on different football events, we first create the ERD for the data provided to us
  • After creating the tables we answer different questions through SQL queries

Entity Relationship Diagram

Create Database

CREATE DATABASE football_data;

Use the database created

USE football_data;

Create Tables

  • Create a table containing all the football events

CREATE TABLE football_events(
id_ods VARCHAR(20),
id_event VARCHAR(20),
sort_order CHAR(3),
time_min CHAR(3),
event_text VARCHAR(1000),
event_type CHAR(3),
event_type2 CHAR(3),
side CHAR(2),
event_team VARCHAR(50),
opponent VARCHAR(50),
player VARCHAR(100),
player2 VARCHAR(100),
player_in VARCHAR(100),
player_out VARCHAR(100),
shot_place CHAR(3),
shot_outcome CHAR(3),
is_goal CHAR(3),
location CHAR(3),
body_part CHAR(3),
assist_method CHAR(3),
situation CHAR(3),
fast_break CHAR(2),
PRIMARY KEY(id_event),
FOREIGN KEY(id_ods) REFERENCES team_details(id_ods),
FOREIGN KEY(event_type) REFERENCES event_type(event_id),
FOREIGN KEY(event_type2) REFERENCES event_type2(event2_id),
FOREIGN KEY(side) REFERENCES side_details(side_id),
FOREIGN KEY(shot_place) REFERENCES shot_details(shot_id),
FOREIGN KEY(shot_outcome) REFERENCES shot_outcome_details(shot_outcome_id),
FOREIGN KEY(location) REFERENCES location_details(location_id),
FOREIGN KEY(body_part) REFERENCES bodypart_details(bodypart_id),
FOREIGN KEY(assist_method) REFERENCES assist_details(assist_id),
FOREIGN KEY(situation) REFERENCES situation_details(situation_id)
);

  • Load the table football events

LOAD DATA LOCAL INFILE '/Users/Kaul10/Desktop/events.csv'
INTO TABLE football_events
FIELDS TERMINATED BY ','
ENCLOSED BY '"'
LINES TERMINATED BY "\n"
IGNORE 1 ROWS
(id_ods, id_event, sort_order, time_min, event_text, event_type, event_type2, side, event_team,
opponent, player, player2, player_in, player_out, shot_place, shot_outcome, is_goal,
location, body_part, assist_method, situation, @fast_break)
SET fast_break = CAST(@fast_break AS CHAR(3));

  • Create the table that gives details about the team, league, goals and odds

CREATE TABLE team_details(
id_ods VARCHAR(20),
id_odsp VARCHAR(20),
link_odsp VARCHAR(500),
adv_stats VARCHAR(10),
game_date date,
league VARCHAR(25),
season CHAR(5),
country VARCHAR(20),
home_team VARCHAR(30),
away_team VARCHAR(30),
fulltime_home_team_goals int,
fulltime_away_team_goals int,
odds_home_win decimal(7,3),
odds_draw decimal(7,3),
odds_away_win decimal(7,3),
PRIMARY KEY(id_ods)
);

  • Load the data into the team details table

LOAD DATA LOCAL INFILE '/Users/Kaul10/Desktop/ginf.csv'
INTO TABLE team_details
FIELDS TERMINATED BY ','
ENCLOSED BY '"'
LINES TERMINATED BY '\n'
IGNORE 1 ROWS
(id_ods, id_odsp, link_odsp, adv_stats, @game_date, league, season, country, home_team,
away_team, fulltime_home_team_goals, fulltime_away_team_goals, odds_home_win,
odds_draw, odds_away_win)
SET game_date = STR_TO_DATE(@game_date, '%m/%d/%y');

SQL Queries

  • Find all the events that Eden Hazard was involved in 2015

WITH football_events_cte AS(
SELECT id_ods, sort_order, event_text, event_type, player, player2, player_in, player_out FROM football_events
),

team_details_cte AS(
SELECT id_ods, season, home_team, away_team FROM team_details
WHERE 1 = 1
AND league = 'EPL'
--AND season = '2015'
),

event_type1_cte AS(
SELECT * FROM event_type
),

event_type2_cte AS(
SELECT * FROM event_type2
),

events_hazard_all AS(
SELECT fce.*, tdc.* FROM football_events_cte fce
INNER JOIN team_details_cte tdc
on fce.id_ods = tdc.id_ods
WHERE 1 = 1
AND player LIKE '%hazard%'
OR player2 LIKE '%hazard%'
OR player_in LIKE '%hazard%'
OR player_out LIKE '%hazard%'
)

SELECT event_type_name, season, COUNT(*) AS event_occurence FROM events_hazard_all eh
LEFT OUTER JOIN event_type1_cte etc1
ON eh.event_type = etc1.event_id
LEFT OUTER JOIN event_type2_cte etc2
ON eh.event_type = etc2.event2_id
WHERE 1 = 1
GROUP BY event_type_name, season
ORDER BY event_type_name, season ASC;

  • Of all the events that Hazard was involved in, how many goals

WITH football_events_cte AS(
SELECT id_ods, sort_order, event_text, event_type, player, player2, player_in, player_out, assist_method, is_goal
FROM football_events
WHERE 1 = 1
),

team_details_cte AS(
SELECT id_ods, season, home_team, away_team
FROM team_details
WHERE 1 = 1
AND league = 'EPL'
),

events_hazard_all AS(
SELECT fce.*, tdc.* FROM football_events_cte fce
INNER JOIN team_details_cte tdc
on fce.id_ods = tdc.id_ods
WHERE 1 = 1
AND (player LIKE '%eden hazard%' or player2 LIKE '%eden hazard%' or player_in LIKE '%eden hazard%' or player_out LIKE '%eden hazard%')
)

final_data as(
select event_text, player, player2, case when player like '%eden hazard%' then 'goal' when player2 like '%eden hazard%' then 'assist' else 'none' end as player_action from events_hazard_all
where 1 = 1
and is_goal = 1
and (player like '%hazard%' or player2 like '%hazard%')
)

select player_action, count(*) as occurences from final_data;

  • Distribution of all different types of events for Chelsea in each season

WITH football_events_cte AS(
SELECT id_ods, sort_order, event_text, event_type, player, player2, player_in, player_out, assist_method, is_goal
FROM football_events
WHERE 1 = 1
),

team_details_cte AS(
SELECT id_ods, season, home_team, away_team
FROM team_details
WHERE 1 = 1
AND league = 'EPL'
),

event_type1_cte AS(
SELECT * FROM event_type
),

event_type2_cte AS(
SELECT * FROM event_type2
),

events_team_all AS(
SELECT fce.*, tdc.*, etc1.*, etc2.* FROM football_events_cte fce
INNER JOIN team_details_cte tdc
ON fce.id_ods = tdc.id_ods
LEFT OUTER JOIN event_type1_cte etc1
ON fce.event_type = etc1.event_id
LEFT OUTER JOIN event_type2_cte etc2
ON fce.event_type = etc2.event2_id
WHERE 1 = 1
AND (home_team LIKE '%ChELSEa%' or away_team LIKE '%ChELSEa%')
),

final_data AS(
SELECT season, CASE WHEN event_type2_name IS NOT NULL THEN event_type2_name ELSE event_type_name END AS event_name
FROM events_team_all
)

SELECT season, event_name, COUNT(*) AS occurences FROM final_data
GROUP BY event_name, season
ORDER BY event_name ASC, season ASC;

  • Distribution of number of goals by league in each season that helps us find out which has been the most exciting league each season

WITH football_events_cte AS(
SELECT id_ods, sort_order, event_text, event_type, player, player2, player_in, player_out, assist_method, is_goal
FROM football_events
WHERE 1 = 1
),

team_details_cte AS(
SELECT id_ods, season, home_team, away_team, league
FROM team_details
WHERE 1 = 1
),

final_data AS(
SELECT * FROM football_events_cte fec
INNER JOIN team_details_cte tdc
ON fec.id_ods = tdc.id_ods
WHERE 1 = 1
AND is_goal = 1
)

SELECT league, season, COUNT(is_goal) AS goals_scored FROM final_data
GROUP BY league, season
ORDER BY season, league;

  • Distribution of te different assist methods for Cesc Fabregas in the different seasons

WITH football_events_cte AS(
SELECT * FROM football_events
WHERE 1 = 1
AND is_goal = 1
AND player2 LIKE '%fabregas%'
),

team_details_cte AS(
SELECT * FROM team_details
WHERE 1 = 1
),

assist_details_cte AS(
SELECT * FROM assist_details
),

final_data AS(
SELECT tdc.season, tdc.league, adc.assist_method FROM football_events_cte fec
INNER JOIN team_details_cte tdc
ON fec.id_ods = tdc.id_ods
LEFT OUTER JOIN assist_details_cte adc
ON fec.assist_method = adc.assist_id
)

SELECT season, assist_method, COUNT(*) as occurences FROM final_data
GROUP BY season, assist_method
ORDER BY season ASC;

  • Who is the best player in the world? Messi or Ronaldo. We can compare, by season, the two by looking at which body part they used to score the goals - Right Foot, Left Foot, Head

WITH football_events_cte AS(
SELECT * FROM football_events
WHERE 1 = 1
AND is_goal = 1
AND (player LIKE '%cristiano ronaldo%' OR player LIKE '%messi%')
--AND (player2 LIKE '%cristiano ronaldo%' or player LIKE '%messi%')
),

team_details_cte AS(
SELECT * FROM team_details
WHERE 1 = 1
),

bodypart_details_cte AS(
SELECT * FROM bodypart_details
),

final_data AS(
SELECT tdc.season, tdc.league, bdc.bodypart, fec.player, fec.player2 FROM football_events_cte fec
INNER JOIN team_details_cte tdc
ON fec.id_ods = tdc.id_ods
LEFT OUTER JOIN bodypart_details_cte bdc
ON fec.body_part = bdc.bodypart_id
)

SELECT season, player, bodypart, COUNT(*) FROM final_data
GROUP BY season, bodypart, player
ORDER BY season ASC, bodypart ASC;

  • How many goalkeeper saves were made in each season for each league to see where the goalkepers have performed the best or have faced the most competition from strikers

WITH football_events_cte AS(
SELECT * FROM football_events
WHERE 1 = 1
AND shot_outcome IS NOT NULL
),

team_details_cte AS(
SELECT * FROM team_details
WHERE 1 = 1
),

shot_outcome_details_cte AS(
SELECT * FROM shot_outcome_details
),

events_team_data AS(
SELECT fec.*, tdc.*, sodc.shot_outcome_id, sodc.shot_outcome AS shot_status FROM football_events_cte fec
INNER JOIN team_details_cte tdc
ON fec.id_ods = tdc.id_ods
LEFT OUTER JOIN shot_outcome_details_cte sodc
ON sodc.shot_outcome_id = fec.shot_outcome
),

goalie_data AS(
SELECT season, league, opponent, shot_status, CASE WHEN shot_status LIKE '%On Target%' OR shot_status LIKE '%Blocked%' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS shot_outcome FROM events_team_data
WHERE 1 = 1
AND shot_outcome_id IS NOT NULL
AND is_goal = 0
),

final_data AS(
SELECT * FROM goalie_data
WHERE 1 = 1
AND shot_outcome = 1
)

SELECT season, league, opponent, COUNT(shot_outcome) AS saves
FROM final_data
GROUP BY season, league, opponent
ORDER BY season ASC, league ASC, COUNT(shot_outcome) DESC
limit 30;

  • Different situations in which the end result was a goal - Corner, Open Play, Set Piece

WITH football_events_cte AS(
SELECT * FROM football_events
WHERE 1 = 1
),

team_details_cte AS(
SELECT * FROM team_details
WHERE 1 = 1
),

situation_details_cte AS(
SELECT situation_id, situation AS actual_situation FROM situation_details
),

final_data AS(
SELECT fec.*, tdc.*, sdc.* FROM football_events_cte fec
INNER JOIN team_details_cte tdc
ON fec.id_ods = tdc.id_ods
LEFT OUTER JOIN situation_details_cte sdc
ON fec.situation = sdc.situation_id
WHERE 1 = 1
AND actual_situation IS NOT NULL
AND is_goal = 1
AND event_team LIKE '%ChELSEa%'
)

SELECT season, actual_situation, COUNT(*) AS occurences
FROM final_data
GROUP BY season, actual_situation
ORDER BY season ASC;

  • Check the Free Kick and Penalty conversion data for Ronaldo and Messi to further add to their best player status

WITH football_events_cte AS(
SELECT * FROM football_events
WHERE 1 = 1
),

team_details_cte AS(
SELECT * FROM team_details
WHERE 1 = 1
),

location_details_cte AS(
SELECT location_id, location AS actual_location FROM location_details
),

situation_details_cte AS(
SELECT situation_id, situation AS actual_situation FROM situation_details
),

final_data AS(
SELECT fec.*, tdc.*, ldc.*, sdc.* FROM football_events_cte fec
INNER JOIN team_details_cte tdc
ON fec.id_ods = tdc.id_ods
LEFT OUTER JOIN location_details_cte ldc
ON ldc.location_id = fec.location
LEFT OUTER JOIN situation_details_cte sdc
ON sdc.situation_id = fec.situation
WHERE 1 = 1
AND is_goal = 1
AND (player LIKE '%cristiano%' or player LIKE '%messi%')
),

final_agg_data AS(
SELECT season, player, actual_location, actual_situation,
CASE WHEN actual_location LIKE '%Penalty%' THEN 'Penalty' WHEN actual_situation LIKE '%Free%' THEN 'Free Kick' ELSE 'Other' END AS set_piece
FROM final_data
)

SELECT season, player, set_piece, COUNT(*) AS occurence FROM final_agg_data
WHERE 1 = 1
AND set_piece NOT LIKE '%Other%'
GROUP BY season, set_piece, player
ORDER BY season, set_piece, player;

  • Which league has the most number of long range attempts from outside the box and even from about 45 yards

WITH football_events_cte AS(
SELECT * FROM football_events
WHERE 1 = 1
),

team_details_cte AS(
SELECT * FROM team_details
WHERE 1 = 1
),

location_details_cte AS(
SELECT location_id, location AS actual_location FROM location_details
WHERE 1 = 1
),

final_data AS(
SELECT fec.*, tdc.*, ldc.* FROM football_events_cte fec
INNER JOIN team_details_cte tdc
ON fec.id_ods = tdc.id_ods
LEFT OUTER JOIN location_details_cte ldc
ON ldc.location_id = fec.location
WHERE 1 = 1
AND is_goal = 1
--AND (player LIKE '%hazard%' or player LIKE '%messi%')
),

final_agg_data AS(
SELECT season, league, actual_location
FROM final_data
WHERE 1 = 1
)

SELECT season, league, actual_location, COUNT(*) AS occurence FROM final_agg_data
WHERE 1 = 1
AND (actual_location LIKE '%Long Range%' OR actual_location LIKE '%More than 35 Yards%' OR actual_location LIKE '%More than 40 Yards%')
GROUP BY season, league, actual_location
ORDER BY season, actual_location;

  • Find players in each league that were Yellow Carded more than 10 times in each league

WITH football_events_cte AS(
SELECT * FROM football_events
WHERE 1 = 1
),

team_details_cte AS(
SELECT * FROM team_details
WHERE 1 = 1
),

event_type_cte AS(
SELECT * FROM event_type
),

football_team_details AS(
SELECT fec.*, tdc.*, etc.* FROM football_events_cte fec
INNER JOIN team_details_cte tdc
ON fec.id_ods = tdc.id_ods
LEFT OUTER JOIN event_type_cte etc
ON fec.event_type = etc.event_id
WHERE 1 = 1
AND event_type_name LIKE '%Yellow card%'
)

SELECT season, league, event_type_name, player, COUNT(*) AS occurence FROM football_team_details
GROUP BY season, league, event_type_name, player
HAVING COUNT(*) >= 10
ORDER BY season ASC, COUNT(*) DESC;
